# Freight Master UI (Vite / Lovable)
# Copy to `.env` in THIS repo only — not into the Next.js API repo.
#
# Rules:
# - Only VITE_* keys are safe for frontend code. Everything else is ignored by Vite (or must not be used).
# - Never add DATABASE_URL, AUTH_SECRET, or AUTH_URL here — those are server-only and will confuse tooling.
# - Do not paste two blocks of the same variable names; the last one wins and will break your setup.

# Next.js API base URL (no trailing slash). Local:
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# If your components use this name instead, keep both values identical:
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Lovable preview runs in the browser on the internet — it cannot reach http://localhost:3000 on your PC.
# Deploy the API (e.g. Vercel) or use a tunnel, then set, for example:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-freight-api.vercel.app
